quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  7,109,"The notables among Pharaoh’s people said, “This is really a skilled magician.”"
  7,110,"“He wants to evict you from your land, so what do you recommend?”"
  7,111,"They said, “Put him off, and his brother, and send heralds to the cities.”"
  7,112,“And let them bring you every skillful magician.”
  7,113,"The magicians came to Pharaoh, and said, “Surely there is a reward for us, if we are the victors.”"
  7,114,"He said, “Yes, and you will be among my favorites.”"
  7,115,"They said, “O Moses! Either you throw, or we are the ones to throw.”"
  7,116,"He said, “You throw!” And when they threw, they beguiled the eyes of the people, and intimidated them, and produced a mighty magic"
  7,117,"And We inspired Moses: “Throw your staff.” And at once, it swallowed what they were faking"
  7,118,"So the truth came to pass, and what they were producing came to nothing"
  7,119,"There they were defeated, and utterly reduced"
  7,120,And the magicians fell to their knees
  7,121,"They said, “We have believed in the Lord of the Worlds.”"
  7,122,“The Lord of Moses and Aaron.”
  7,123,"Pharaoh said, “Did you believe in Him before I have given you permission? This is surely a conspiracy you schemed in the city, in order to expel its people from it. You will surely know.”"
  7,124,“I will cut off your hands and your feet on opposite sides; then I will crucify you all.”
  7,125,"They said, “It is to our Lord that we will return.”"
  7,126,"“You are taking vengeance on us only because we have believed in the signs of our Lord when they have come to us.” “Our Lord! Pour out patience upon us, and receive our souls in submission.”"